original: Österlund, Carl Birger, läroverksadjunkt, Uddevalla, f. 7/3’/89 i Grönahög, Älvsb. 1., av Frans Ö. o. Ellen Johansson. G. 25 m. Svea Håkansson. Barn: Birgitta f. 26, Gunilla 28, Gudrun 36, Ragnhild 38. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. real 10, fil. mag. i Gbg 17, provår v. Gbgs h. latin 20-21. Vik. lektor i Umeå 18-19, e. lär. där 19-20, i Vänersb. 21-22, vik. adj. i Enköp. 22-23’, e. lär. v. Malmö realsk. 23-24, adj. i Skellefteå 24, adj. i moder sm. o. hist. m. samh :lära v. Uddevalla h. a. 1. sed. 31. RVO.
translated: Österlund, Carl Birger, high school teacher, Uddevalla, born on March 7th, 1889 in Grönahög, Älvsborg County, son of Frans Ö. and Ellen Johansson. Married on May 25th to Svea Håkansson. Children: Birgitta, born in 1926, Gunilla in 1928, Gudrun in 1936, Ragnhild in 1938. Completed high school at Gothenburg's Royal Real Gymnasium in 1910, received a Bachelor's Degree in Gothenburg in 1917, spent a probationary year at Gothenburg's Royal Latin School from 1920 to 1921. Acting lecturer in Umeå from 1918 to 1919, regular teacher there from 1919 to 1920, in Vänersborg from 1921 to 1922, acting adjunct in Enköping from 1922 to 1923, regular teacher at Malmö Real School from 1923 to 1924, adjunct in Skellefteå in 1924, adjunct in mother tongue and history with social studies at Uddevalla's high school since 1931. Awarded with the Order of Vasa (RVO).
